      <acttitle>Health Act</acttitle>
      <title>Health Hazard Regulation</title>
      <content>
        <section toc="false">
          <marginalnote>Definition inclusion</marginalnote>
          <sectionnumber>1</sectionnumber>
          <sectiontext>The definition of <term>health hazard</term> in section 1 of the <actname>Health Act</actname> includes milk for human consumption that has not been pasteurized as required under the <actname>Milk Industry Act</actname> at a dairy plant licensed under the <actname>Milk Industry Act</actname>.</sectiontext>
        </section>
        <provisionsnote>[Provisions of the <actname>Health Act</actname>, R.S.B.C. 1996, c. 179, relevant to the enactment of this regulation: sections 1, 8, 11]</provisionsnote>
      </content>
    </reg>
